Import Intent Data to an Einstein Intent Set

You can use Einstein Intent Sets to move utterances and entities between Salesforce orgs.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To build and manage Einstein Bots:	
Customize Application

OR

Modify Metadata

OR

Manage Bots


To manage intent sets and bot training:	
Customize Application

OR

Modify Metadata

OR

Manage Bots

OR

Manage Bots Training Data

Using the Quick find tool in Setup, type in Einstein Intent Sets to access the Einstein Intent Set menu.
Create a three-column CSV file with headers MlDomainName, MlIntentName, Utterance, and Language. In an Intent set, MlDomainName (Capital M, lowercase l) refers to the intent set API name. 
Log into Data Loader, select Intent Utterance as the Object, map your fields to MlDomainName, MlIntentName, and Utterance.
Select the directory where your success and error files are saved. Click Finish.

Return to the Bot Builder, select the dialog you want to add the intent data. In the Intent Sets section, click Add Intent.
Select your intent from the list then save your changes.
title: Importing Intent Data into Einstein Intent Set
